# TASK FILE TEMPLATE

Every task you write must follow this exact structure:

\`\`\`markdown
# Task [ID]: [Title]
Status: PENDING | IN PROGRESS | DONE
Can run in parallel with: [task ID or NONE]

## PLAN
- Goal: [one sentence]
- Inputs: [what this task receives/depends on]
- Outputs: [what this task produces]
- Constraints: [what NOT to touch, limits]
- Open Questions: [anything needing my clarification before starting]

## IMPLEMENT
### Files Touched
- CREATE: [list of new files]
- MODIFY: [list of existing files]
- DO NOT TOUCH: [explicit exclusions]

### Implementation Notes
[key technical decisions, patterns to follow]

## VALIDATE
### Unit Tests
- [ ] [test case 1]
- [ ] [test case 2]

### E2E Tests
- [ ] [user flow or API call that proves it works]

### Success Criteria
- [ ] All unit tests pass
- [ ] E2E test passes
- [ ] No regressions in existing tests
- [ ] Code follows project conventions

## ITERATE
### Outcome
[filled after execution — what actually happened]

### Knowledge Updates
[what should be added to memory-bank after this task]

### Follow-ups
[new tasks this created, open issues]
\`\`\`

